Subject: [patch] 2.3.48: simple bootloader optimizations, etc.
Sender: linux-kernel-owner@vger.kernel.org
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org
X-Lkml-Link: https://lkml.org/lkml/2000/3/3/5

Shrinks the size of the bootsector code while providing more functionality
(able to now boot 360/720k diskettes).
Also tidies up comments to at&t syntax, adds a few new comments.
Untested atm, but the only thing I've done since 2.3.41 is sync it up with
the other changes in arch/i386/boot.
[ 
http://www.northlink.com/~stiker/bootcode-2.3.48.diff
 ]
Chris Noe
